WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.651
All living things

00:00:01.651 --> 00:00:03.303
need food to

00:00:03.303 --> 00:00:04.955
grow. While animals

00:00:04.955 --> 00:00:06.606
find food, plants

00:00:06.606 --> 00:00:08.258
make their own

00:00:08.258 --> 00:00:09.910
using sunlight.

00:00:09.910 --> 00:00:11.404
Inside plant leaves,

00:00:11.404 --> 00:00:12.898
there is a

00:00:12.898 --> 00:00:14.392
green pigment called

00:00:14.392 --> 00:00:15.887
chlorophyll. It acts

00:00:15.887 --> 00:00:17.381
like a solar

00:00:17.381 --> 00:00:18.875
panel to capture

00:00:18.875 --> 00:00:20.369
light.

00:00:20.369 --> 00:00:22.046
Plants also absorb

00:00:22.046 --> 00:00:23.723
water from the

00:00:23.723 --> 00:00:25.399
soil through roots,

00:00:25.399 --> 00:00:27.076
and pull in

00:00:27.076 --> 00:00:28.753
carbon dioxide gas

00:00:28.753 --> 00:00:30.429
from the air.

00:00:30.429 --> 00:00:32.169
Sunlight splits water

00:00:32.169 --> 00:00:33.909
and gas into

00:00:33.909 --> 00:00:35.649
glucose sugar for

00:00:35.649 --> 00:00:37.390
food, and releases

00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:39.130
clean oxygen for

00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:40.870
us to breathe.

